com.inqwell.any.jms

Interface MessageI

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Any, Serializable
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    BytesMessageI, MapMessageI, ObjectMessageI, StreamMessageI, TextMessageI
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AnyBytesMessage, AnyMapMessage, AnyMessage, AnyObjectMessage, AnyStreamMessage, AnyTextMessage

    public interface MessageI
extends Any
    Access to a JMS message within the Any framework.

    Author:
    tom

      • getProperty

        Any getProperty(Any name,
                Any type)
        Get a named message property according to the supplied type. The type argument is used to resolve the underlying property type and takes its value from the appropriate method on javax.jms.Message, for example getDoubleProperty(String name).
        Parameters:
        name - the name of the property
        type - the value to which the property is assigned. This value is also returned.
        Returns:
        the typeargument.
        Throws:
        AnyRuntimeException - Any exception that occurs in the underlying JMS provider implementation is thrown as a AnyRuntimeException

      • setProperty

        void setProperty(Any name,
                 Any type)
        Set a named message property according to the supplied type. The type argument is used to resolve the underlying property type to determine the method to call on javax.jms.Message, for example setDoubleProperty(String name, double value).
        Parameters:
        name - the name of the property
        type - the value to which the property is set.
        Throws:
        AnyRuntimeException - Any exception that occurs in the underlying JMS provider implementation is thrown as a AnyRuntimeException

      • getClientProperties

        Map getClientProperties()
        Returns all client properties contained within this JMS message as a Map. The property values are universally converted to StringIs.
        Returns:
        A Map containing the property names as keys and their string representations as values.
